<subSubSection id="DEAC0E08DA5ABCE2EEE9E4BDC7D4C06B" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="CDB6D66FE17F7727DC6942A6CB815D46" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06BCEDD5E4421BB79B4CDB79D5DD79BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Described from Puerto Rico, America on 
<taxonomicName id="FAAF957E7085B058BDDCC335235DFBAA" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Panicum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Panicum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72206C9EF78B983DCD8BB9AB39C528D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Panicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves, this species is recorded from Egypt and Uganda by 
<bibRefCitation id="E497FAAF0453FE7FC2133032932AAC72" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" author="Ritchie, JM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomology (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" pagination="261 - 282" refId="B14" refString="Ritchie, JM, 1974. A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae. Journal of Entomology (B) 43: 261 - 282" title="A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" volume="43" year="1974">Ritchie (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, with 
<taxonomicName id="C1303CAD0A60DB4EFA675EAAC01C5FD1" genus="P." lsidName="P. aegyptiacus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis id="02BDCE3400EB711CC66C177883E77242" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Priesner placed as a synonym. This is one of two species from China in which the thorax is yellow (
<figureCitation id="C681DA166321F28F22B14FCB0F33657B" captionStart="Figures 17–22" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 22. Podothrips adult colour patterns 17 P. lucasseni 18 P. odonaspicola 19 P. semiflavus 20 P. femoralis sp. nov. 21 P. sasacola. Some important features of femoralis sp. nov. 22 mesopresternum and metathoracic sternopleural sutures. Scale bars: 200 microns." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/349333" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), but 
<taxonomicName id="D5AFCDCA18E06579E3E9EFFBE0B9A221" genus="P." lsidName="P. luteus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="luteus">
<emphasis id="0BD7FC864B86000037E0C82210AD945A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. luteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taiwan has abdominal segments 
<normalizedToken id="3880FCE269B9BE00AEB7B6B89F909CB2" originalValue="VIII–X">VIII-X</normalizedToken>
brown, whereas the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName id="EB3EBE0A330413B403954434A5DFB8D8" genus="P." lsidName="P. semiflavus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="semiflavus">
<emphasis id="25CB39D1CFC615884085E6A3A95AA76F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. semiflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost yellow with just the basal third of the tube brown (
<figureCitation id="C93C1EB8E3A2704003F436CA82653E3B" captionStart="Figures 17–22" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 22. Podothrips adult colour patterns 17 P. lucasseni 18 P. odonaspicola 19 P. semiflavus 20 P. femoralis sp. nov. 21 P. sasacola. Some important features of femoralis sp. nov. 22 mesopresternum and metathoracic sternopleural sutures. Scale bars: 200 microns." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/349333" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). One female from Guangdong has been studied here, and this is the first record of the species from China.
</paragraph>
